{"word":"H8327 - שָׁרַשׁ - shârash - shaw-rash' - Root","slug":"H8327","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׁרַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shârash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shaw-rash'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Root"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - sha&#x0302;rash</b> - <i>shaw-rash'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>root</i>, that is, strike into the soil, or (by implication) to pluck from it: - (take, cause to take) root (out)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8328\">H8328</a>, <a href=\"#/H8329\">H8329</a>, <a href=\"#/H8331\">H8331</a>"}]}